dss = Event.create!(name: "Dominican Success Stories", venue: "Memorial Chapel", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,9,30), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,11,30),
	description: "Dominicans are a resilient people, shaped by our history, our diaspora, our sense of community. Join us
in an expose of Dominicans whose stories will inspire our own success stories. In line with the theme of
this year's conference, we hope to explore how individual success can be a medium for social justice by
changing the landscape of the cultural identities that are represented in different industries. Panelists
will also discuss if and how assimilation has played a role in their success. This workshop will be
moderated to include an in depth and collaborative discussion from student attendees.", show_in_program: true)
Event.create!(name: "Lunch", venue: "Backham Hall", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,11,45), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,1,15))
Event.create!(name: "Mami Echate Pa ‘Ka: The Hyper-sexualization of Women", venue: "CFA Hall", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,13,30), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,15),
	description: "Whether you live in Santo Domingo, Washington Heights or Lawrence, Massachusetts, as a woman of color, it is very likely that you know what it's like to be hollered at or piropia' on the street. In this workshop we will be discussing male and female interactions within our community. We will leverage our personal experiences and use media to analyze the ways in which we allow our gender to impact how we relate to one another. This discussion will be give a true taste of what class is like at Wesleyan, facilitated by one of our most radical professors, Bob Steele. Come prepared to let your voice be heard in rich discussion as you share your thoughts, experiences and personal opinions.", show_in_program: true)
Event.create!(name: "The Truth Behind Bars: The Prison Industrial Complex", venue: "Crowell Concert Hall", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,13,30), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,15),
	description: "Have you noticed a shortage of Dominican men and men of color, in general, in your classrooms? This discussion will address one of the probable causes of the under-representation of Black and Latino men in education: the prison industrial complex. With different panelists representing academia, prison policy, reform movements, and the prison and deportation experience, we aim to explore all perspectives of this problem. Topics discussed will include the war on drugs, stop and frisk, and the privatization of the prison system. This discussion will have you at the edge of your seat as you learn about the gravity of this situation.", show_in_program: true)
Event.create!(name: "Breakout Sessions", venue: "Various", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,15,30), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,16,30),
	description: "In this conference, we have allotted an hour for different student or professional organizations to propose and present a workshop on a social justice topic of their interest. Workshops will include: Transforming Community: Education, Leadership, Service (Avanzando Nuestra Comunidad a Travez de la Educacion) with Teach for America, City Year and the Peace Corps; Decolonizing Our Minds- A discussion on Internalized Oppression; Students Making Change- Dreamer Movement and Immigration Reform; and a workshop about current events in DR. To submit a proposal email us at wesndsc@gmail.com.", show_in_program: true)
Event.create!(name: "E Pa'lante Que Vamos, Recordando Nuestras Raíces: Organization Fair", venue: "Exley Lobbey", start_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,17), end_time: DateTime.new(2013,3,30,20),
	description: "This will be an organization fair which will include over ten organizations that are working to provide solutions to the social justice issues discussed during the conference. This will be your chance to participate in career-advancing networking and learn about volunteer opportunities to make a difference now! Confirmed organizations include but are not limited to Teach for America, City Year, the Peace Corps, Dominicans on Wall Street, the Society for Hispanic Professional Engineers, The National Latina Institute for Reproductive Health, Dominican York Proyecto Grafica and more. This fair will occur concurrently with our formal dinner, to give participants ample room and time to network. Conference participants will be assigned to one of two groups to attend dinner, alternating between dinner and the fair.", show_in_program: true)
